<paragraph id="C42B36FEFFE86A57FD2795571A78BFBC" blockId="19.[731,1324,782,1205]" pageId="19" pageNumber="777">
<subSubSection id="8C8E6575FFE86A57FD2795571A16B848" pageId="19" pageNumber="777" type="reference_group">
<emphasis id="F6E0EAECFFE86A57FD2795571D76B819" bold="true" box="[731,886,782,811]" pageId="19" pageNumber="777">Taxonomy.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFE86A57FC7995571DBDB860" authority="Aellen, 1957" authorityName="Aellen" authorityYear="1957" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Pipistrellus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="777" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="permixtus" subGenus="Pipistrellus">Pipistrellus (Pipistrellus) permixtus Aellen, 1957</taxonomicName>
, 
<materialsCitation id="74FC3CA3FFE86A57FC32956C1A16B848" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3783319451" pageId="19" pageNumber="777">
“ 
<collectingRegion id="0650F81CFFE86A57FC24956C1A90B860" box="[984,1168,821,850]" country="Tanzania" name="Dar es Salaam" pageId="19" pageNumber="777">Dar es Salam</collectingRegion>
[sic], Tanganyika [= 
<collectingCountry id="BC83766EFFE86A57FC8A95001DFCB848" box="[886,1020,857,890]" name="Tanzania" pageId="19" pageNumber="777">Tanzania</collectingCountry>
].”
</materialsCitation>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8C8E6575FFE86A57FD2795DD1A78BFBC" pageId="19" pageNumber="777" type="discussion">
Taxonomy of 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFE86A57FC5995DD1A45B893" authorityName="Aellen" authorityYear="1957" box="[933,1093,900,929]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Pipistrellus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="777" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="permixtus">P. permixtus</taxonomicName>
is currently uncertain. It seems to be related to Palearctic 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFE86A57FD2795961D67B8C2" authorityName="Kaup" authorityYear="1829" box="[731,871,975,1008]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Pipistrellus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="777" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Pipistrellus</taxonomicName>
, and because the only known specimen was found at port 
<collectingRegion id="0650F81CFFE86A57FB9C95A71B25BF25" box="[1120,1317,1022,1047]" country="Tanzania" name="Dar es Salaam" pageId="19" pageNumber="777">Dar-es-Salaam</collectingRegion>
, there are speculations that it might have been a stowaway on a ship from some Palearctic region. Monotypic.
</subSubSection>
</paragraph>
