<subSubSection id="8C8E6575FFE86A57FF849E791F99B38B" pageId="19" pageNumber="777" type="conservation">
<paragraph id="C42B36FEFFE86A57FF849E791F99B38B" blockId="19.[118,1326,1217,2312]" pageId="19" pageNumber="777">
<emphasis id="F6E0EAECFFE86A57FF849E791FD3B373" bold="true" box="[120,467,2080,2113]" pageId="19" pageNumber="777">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Classified as Data Deficient on The IUCN Red List. The 
<collectingRegion id="0650F81CFFE86A57FB339E791EDAB35B" country="Tanzania" name="Dar es Salaam" pageId="19" pageNumber="777">Dar-es-Salaam</collectingRegion>
Pipistrelle is known from only a single specimen collected at a port in eastern 
<collectingCountry id="BC83766EFFE86A57FF849E361EF7B3A2" box="[120,247,2159,2192]" name="Tanzania" pageId="19" pageNumber="777">Tanzania</collectingCountry>
in 1905. Surveys are needed to determine its status and relationship to other species of 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFE86A57FEF59EC11F95B38B" authorityName="Kaup" authorityYear="1829" box="[265,405,2200,2233]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Pipistrellus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="777" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Pipistrellus</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
